This message is automatically generated., Thanks, Ratandeep! I agree with your detailed analysis. For your description "One scenario in which this loop will never break is when the Namenode tries to schedule a new replica on the same node on which we actually corrupted the block.", {{BlockManager}}'s {{markBlockAsCorrupt}} function will ask DN to invalidate the corrupt block after NN receives block report from that DN. So if the replication is scheduled after that, then the loop should break. We can fix the test code to make sure the correct order of events happen. But that is more complicated.

For the first loop, does it just reduce the chance? If the test runs on slow machine, maybe 3 is still not enough. We can delay the start of 3rd DN by moving  {{cluster.startDataNodes(conf, 1, true, null, null, null);}} after the loop check; but that doesn't prevent the the replication to finish quickly on the same DN with old corrupted block., Thanks [~mingma] for having a look at this.
 
You are right. For the first loop it just make it  less likely for the test to fail. 
Delaying the start of the 3rd DN seems like a nice approach.
For the second loop:
How can we make sure that the replication is scheduled after a block report is publish by the DN containing the corrupt block?, Ratandeep, here is what you could do to make sure all events are ordered properly. 

1. Set {{DFS_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_KEY}} to be some large value.
2. Use {{DataNodeTestUtils.triggerHeartbeat}} to control when HB is sent.

Then you will do something like:

1. Make sure the first dn has sent blockreport with corrupted block. For example, use {{DataNodeTestUtils.spyOnBposToNN}}.
2. Invoke {{cluster.getNamesystem().getBlockManager().computeDatanodeWork();}}. This will make sure invalidation request is queued to the first dn's DatanodeDescriptor and replication request is queued to the second dn's DatanodeDescriptor.
3. Invoke {{DataNodeTestUtils.triggerHeartbeat}} on the first dn to completes the first invalidation. Then invoke {{DataNodeTestUtils.triggerHeartbeat}} on the second dn to completes the replication., Thanks [~mingma] . I'll update the patch to reflect the method discussed., | (x) *{color:red}-1 overall{color}* |
